Then comes the creative step you mentioned.

“…once you discover them it’s about creating with them.”

That feels like an important distinction.

Discovery identifies existing invariants.

Creation chooses and combines invariants to build new structures.

A bridge doesn’t invent gravity.

It composes with it.

Music doesn’t invent harmonic relationships.

It composes with them.

Programming doesn’t invent logical implication.

It composes with it.

The mathematician discovers a symmetry.

The engineer exploits it.

The artist evokes it.

The biologist evolves through it.

Different activities, same invariant.

